SUBCOMMITTEE CONSIDERATION
On March 25, 2025, the Subcommittee on Health met in an open
markup session, a quorum being present, to consider H.R. 1969.
Representative Miller-Meeks offered an amendment in the nature
of a substitute, which would extend the program through 2026;
clarify the interplay with other emergent suicide prevention au-
thorities; and mandate the use of the Columbia-Suicide Severity
Rating Scale, which is a screening tool. This amendment was
adopted by a recorded vote of 7 yeas, 5 noes. A motion by Rep-
resentative Van Orden of Wisconsin to order H.R. 1969, as amend-
ed, favorably forwarded to the full Committee on Veterans Affairs
was agreed to by voice vote.
COMMITTEE CONSIDERATION
