the Veterans SPORT Act, ensuring the availability of adaptive
sports or recreation prosthetic limbs, including artificial hand ‘‘ter-
minal devices,’’ by recognizing them as clinically necessary for vet-
erans suffering from limb loss. This amendment to the amendment
in the nature of a substitute was agreed to by voice vote.
